	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><persName>S. GERSTMAN &#38; CO.</persName>&#44;</p>
				<p>Commission Merchants</p>
				<p><placeName>186 Congress &#38; 85 St. Julian Sts.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>SAVANNAH&#44; GA</placeName>.</p>
				<p><persName role="author">S. GERSTMAN</persName>.  <persName>W. BARNETT</persName>.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Savannah</placeName>&#44; <date>April 17 1866</date></p>
				<p rend="align(center)"><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
				<p rend="align(center)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I have recd the<lb/> Tafelas &#38;c and have collected<lb/> all the money except for<lb/> two which the party are not<lb/> in town but will be here<lb/> in a few days&#44; when I will<lb/> forward you a draft for<lb/> the full amount&#44; I would<lb/> advise you if possible to<lb/> come out to inaugurate the<lb/> B.B. Lodge here as I am confident<lb/> that you could get over 50<lb/> subscribers for the Occident<lb/> &#38; could sell over 100 copies<lb/> of your daily Prayers&#44; and probably</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>some other of your publications.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have the Honor to be very</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Respectfully yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Brother <persName role="author">Phillip Walker</persName></p>
				<p>P.S. Brother <persName>Gartensteig</persName> send<lb/> his thanks for your attention to the<lb/> payment of his dues&#44; you will<lb/> please send the <persName role="author">Rev. Simon Gerstman</persName><lb/> a set of <add>Hebrew&#63;</add> polish minhag<lb/> with english translation&#44; also<lb/> <del>for</del> one <sic>sett</sic> Portuguese <add>Hebrew&#63;</add><lb/> and also one prayer book for<lb/> <add>Hebrew&#63;</add> with english since<lb/> writing the above I have recd the<lb/> balance of the money &#36; 20.00 is for<lb/> the 2 Bibles &#36;25.00 for the other<lb/> Books &#38; &#36;4.00 for <persName role="author">Rev. Simon<lb/> Gerstmans</persName> Occident for which you<lb/> will please acknowledge receipt</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p><addressee>Rev Mr. Leeser</addressee>&#33;</p>
				<p>As personally unknown each other&#44;<lb/> I would respectfully ask of you<lb/> to send me some manuscripts&#44;<lb/> of your works&#44; or talmudical&#44;<lb/> also different <sic>adresses</sic> delivered<lb/> by you&#44; and different subjects.<lb/> I should be very obliging to<lb/> you.  You can send them to<lb/> me per express&#44; such as you think<lb/> will be useful to me. You can<lb/> send them along when you send<lb/> me the other books.</p>
				<p><sic>Hopping</sic> to hear from you<lb/> by return.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I remain Rev</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your most good servant</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">Simon Gerstmann</persName></p>
		</body>
	</text>
